      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4>Optional Activity</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A popular band is trying to raise at least $20,000 for charity by holding multiple concerts at a park. It plans to sell tickets at $25 each. For each 2-hour concert, the band would need to pay the park $1,250 in fees for security, cleaning, and traffic services.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The band needs to find the combinations of number of tickets sold, t, and number of concerts held, c, that would allow it to reach its fundraising goal.</p>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-content-id=\"0696afdc-c2cf-4c54-9134-34e556c62489\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <p>1. Write an inequality to represent the constraints in this situation.</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p><span>\\(25t-1,250c\\geq20,000\\)</span><br></p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-content-id=\"d2125f10-bc78-4b35-9959-e3278fdf16dc\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <p>2. Graph the solutions to the inequality on the coordinate plane.<br><br><img alt=\"Blank grid, origin O. Horizontal axis, number of tickets sold, scale is 0 to 2,500 by 500&rsquo;s. Vertical axis, number of concerts held, scale is 0 to 24 by 4&rsquo;s.\" height=\"271\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/810a175d377aa8764cc7fd6a00a691ca977f77f4\" width=\"500\"></p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p><img alt=\"Graph of an inequality. Number of concerts held. Number of tickets sold.\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/c60946be3d346369f604baa00e8a630a084e6bdd\"></p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-content-id=\"910a3bf2-d091-4d39-9359-64f259dcb64a\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <p>3. Name two possible combinations of number of tickets sold and number of concerts held that would allow the band to meet its goal.</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>For example:&nbsp;<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=\"false\"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1000&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;2&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=\"false\"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-10-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\">\n        <nobr aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-57\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-58\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-59\">(</span><span id=\"MathJax-Span-60\">1000</span><span id=\"MathJax-Span-61\">,</span><span id=\"MathJax-Span-62\">2</span><span id=\"MathJax-Span-63\">)</span></span></span></nobr><span role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\">\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n            <mn>1000</mn>\n            <mo>,</mo>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n          </math></span>\n      </span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span data-mathml='&lt;math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=\"false\"&gt;(&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;1400&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo&gt;,&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;mn&gt;5&lt;/mn&gt;&lt;mo stretchy=\"false\"&gt;)&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/math&gt;' id=\"MathJax-Element-11-Frame\" role=\"presentation\" tabindex=\"0\">\n        <nobr aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-64\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-65\"><span id=\"MathJax-Span-66\">(</span><span id=\"MathJax-Span-67\">1400</span><span id=\"MathJax-Span-68\">,</span><span id=\"MathJax-Span-69\">5</span><span id=\"MathJax-Span-70\">)</span></span></span></nobr>\n      </span><br></p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End --><br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-content-id=\"8a242025-0002-4626-b611-ddceba8a6913\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <div>\n      <p>4. Which combination of tickets and concerts would mean&nbsp;<em>more</em>&nbsp;money for charity:</p>\n    </div>\n    <div>\n      <div>a. 1,300 tickets and 10 concerts, or 1,300 tickets and 5 concerts?</div>\n      <div>b. 1,600 tickets and 16 concerts, or 1,200 tickets and 9 concerts?</div>\n      <div>c. 2,000 tickets and 4 concerts, or 2,500 tickets and 10 concerts?</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <div>Compare your answer:</div>\n    <div>\n      <div>a. 1,300 tickets and 5 concerts</div>\n      <div>b. 1,600 tickets and 16 concerts.</div>\n      <div>c. 2,500 tickets and 10 concerts</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>"
    }
